/div><div class="col col-sm-5" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1"><div class="social-share-top" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0"><div class="component-social-share default" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves&amp;t=How%20to%20Protect%20Your%20New%20Bike%20from%20Thieves" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves&amp;t=How%20to%20Protect%20Your%20New%20Bike%20from%20Thieves" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0.1">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item twitter" data-href="https://twitter.com/share?text=How%20to%20Protect%20Your%20New%20Bike%20from%20Thieves&amp;via=GQMagazine&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter"><a href="https://twitter.com/share?text=How%20to%20Protect%20Your%20New%20Bike%20from%20Thieves&amp;via=GQMagazine&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves" target="_blank" aria-label="Twitter" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0.1">Twitter</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><h2 class="dek" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.3"></h2><div class="body-text" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4"><div class="embed image" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.0"><figure class="embedded-image" data-type="image"><div class="image-content"><div class="component-rendition"><div class="component-image loaded"><span><img src="http://media.gq.com/photos/55b94460b6a585c04cb5aedd/master/w_768/bike-gif5.gif" alt="bike-gif5.gif"></span></div></div><div class="component-social-share default"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves&amp;t=bike-gif5.gif"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves&amp;t=bike-gif5.gif" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item pinterest" data-href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F55b94460b6a585c04cb5aedd%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2Fbike-gif5.gif&amp;description=bike-gif5.gif"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F55b94460b6a585c04cb5aedd%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2Fbike-gif5.gif&amp;description=bike-gif5.gif" target="_blank" aria-label="Pinterest"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Pinterest</span></a></div></div></div></figure></div><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.1">So you&#x2019;ve decided to join the all-powerful bike lobby? Congratulations! Here, have a complimentary pennyfarthing for contributing to America&#x2019;s 60% surge in ridership over the past decade. Now for the bad news: The spike in ridership has come alongside a dramatic spike in bike theft, too. </p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.2">Sure, some scale of theft is inevitable. But there are still some simple steps you can take to defend yourself from would-be thieves. </p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.3"><strong>STEP 1: PREVENTION</strong><br>One of the best ways to safeguard your bike is also one of the most commonly overlooked: <strong>knowing its serial number.</strong> </p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.5">&#x201C;It&#x2019;s the single most important thing you can have if the bike goes missing,&#x201D; says Bryan Hance of <a href="https://bikeindex.org/">Bike Index</a>, a digital bike registry. Photos and unique characteristics &#x2014; a sticker here, a funky component there &#x2014; are helpful for post-theft identification, but the serial number &#x201C;is the only thing that&#x2019;s going to prove that particular bike being sold on craigslist is yours.&#x201D;</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.6">You don&#x2019;t need to be a bike wizard to find that number either. It&#x2019;s typically engraved beneath the bottom bracket or on one of a few other easy-to-spot places.</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.7">Registering that information with the police can aid in recovery on a local scale. But these municipal databases suffer from a critical flaw: Bikes are highly mobile, and pro thieves often ship their hauls far away to reduce the risk of being caught. &#x201C;Bike theft isn&#x2019;t a local problem,&#x201D; says Officer Matt Friedman, who heads San Francisco&#x2019;s anti-bike-theft unit. &#x201C;It&#x2019;s a universal problem.&#x201D;</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.8">Enter the Internet. Several services&#x2014;including the aforementioned Bike Index&#x2014;allow cyclists to register their serial numbers for free. The result: Universal, searchable repositories for police and private citizens to track stolen bikes anywhere. That way, a bike stolen in Boston and confiscated in Oakland can still find its way back home.</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.9">&#x201C;Instead of these little balkanized databases we have this one crazy big one,&#x201D; Hance says.</p><div class="embed callout" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.a"><div class="callout small" data-type="callout"><div class="embed pullquote" data-type="pullquote"><span><blockquote><p>&quot;Your bike doesn&#x2019;t have to be impossible to steal. It just has to be harder to steal than the bikes around it.&quot;</p></blockquote></span><div class="pullquote-share twitter"><a class="pullquote-share-icon" href="https://twitter.com/share?via=GQ&amp;text=%22%26quot%3BYour%20bike%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20be%20impossible%20to%20steal.%20It%20just%20has%20to%20be%20harder%20to%20steal%20than%20the%20bikes%20around%20it.%26quot%3B%22" target="_blank" title="Share on Twitter"><span class="label">Twitter</span></a></div></div></div></div><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.b"><strong>STEP 2: PROTECTION</strong><br>You&#x2019;re almost ready to ride. First, though, you&#x2019;ll need a good lock.</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.c">&#x201C;But my bike is garbage!&#x201D; you might say. &#x201C;No one would want that rusted heap plastered with Lisa Frank stickers.&#x201D; Then a thief hauls your rusted heap plastered and its Lisa Frank stickers off to a chop shop.</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.d">The truth is <strong>most thieves don&#x2019;t care about a bike&#x2019;s condition or branding.</strong> &#x201C;I talk to a lot of people that say things like &#x2018;I&#x2019;m glad that it looks kind of crappy because thieves won&#x2019;t want it,&#x2019;&#x201D; says Emily Thibodeau, owner of Hub Bicycle in Cambridge, Mass.  &#x201C;And that is completely untrue.&#x201D;</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.e">&#x201C;They are looking for the easiest bike to steal,&#x201D; she says. &#x201C;That&#x2019;s pretty much it.&#x201D;</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.f">You don&#x2019;t need to go full Pee Wee Herman when you lock up &#x2014; not that it helped him, anyway &#x2014; but if you&#x2019;re riding in an urban environment, you&#x2019;ll want something beefier than the cheapo coil from your childhood Huffy.  </p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.g">&#x201C;Cable locks are terrible,&#x201D; Hance says. &#x201C;You can go to Home Depot and get a tool for $40 to cut right through them.&#x201D;</p><div class="embed image" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.h"><figure class="embedded-image" data-type="image"><div class="image-content"><div class="component-rendition"><div class="component-image loaded"><span><img src="http://media.gq.com/photos/55b93cbe624390b349811eed/master/w_768/34c6ac_8b1e7ebe3e4445c09040239813d613ce.jpg" alt="34c6ac_8b1e7ebe3e4445c09040239813d613ce.jpg"></span></div></div><div class="component-social-share default"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves&amp;t=34c6ac_8b1e7ebe3e4445c09040239813d613ce.jpg"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves&amp;t=34c6ac_8b1e7ebe3e4445c09040239813d613ce.jpg" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item pinterest" data-href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F55b93cbe624390b349811eed%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2F34c6ac_8b1e7ebe3e4445c09040239813d613ce.jpg&amp;description=34c6ac_8b1e7ebe3e4445c09040239813d613ce.jpg"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F55b93cbe624390b349811eed%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2F34c6ac_8b1e7ebe3e4445c09040239813d613ce.jpg&amp;description=34c6ac_8b1e7ebe3e4445c09040239813d613ce.jpg" target="_blank" aria-label="Pinterest"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Pinterest</span></a></div></div></div></figure></div><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.i">If you don&#x2019;t mind lugging the extra weight, bulky chain locks offer the best protection since they are the most difficult to cut. For most riders though, U-locks are adequate. (At least now that they can&#x2019;t be <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LahDQ2ZQ3e0">hacked with basic Bic pens</a>.) <strong>Among U-locks, smaller is better because it leaves less room for a thief to get good leverage.</strong> Just make sure you secure the frame of the bike, or you may return to a single forlorn wheel, lock fully intact. Good luck riding that home! </p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.j">It should go without saying, but ensure you lock your rig to an immovable object, too. Though rare, thieves have been known to deploy dummy poles or saw through trees to pilfer bikes. And if you have easily detachable components&#x2014;wheels with quick release skewers, lights, panniers&#x2014;either lock them up or take them with you. If you don&#x2019;t take them, a thief gladly will. (Quick release skewers can also be replaced with more secure locking mechanisms.)</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.k">As for locking technique, <strong>one of the most secure&#x2014;albeit counterintuitive&#x2014;methods involves placing a u-lock around only the rear rim and inside the rear triangle</strong>. Popularized by bike guru Sheldon Brown, the <a href="https://www.missionbicycle.com/blog/lock-and-roll-secrets-rear-triangle">eponymous locking method</a> makes it impossible to remove the rear rim from the rest of the bike, thus anchoring everything without actually placing the lock around the frame. </p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.l">Other effective methods involve using multiple locks, or using multiple <em>types</em> of locks. Both strategies force crooks to up their games, with the latter also requiring them to have several tools on hand.</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.m">&#x201C;Bike theft is about time,&#x201D; Friedman says. &#x201C;No lock is 100 percent theft-proof. But if you can slow down a thief, then you&#x2019;re doing your job.&#x201D;</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.n">In other words, securing a bike is like that old joke about outrunning a bear: Your bike doesn&#x2019;t have to be impossible to steal. It just has to be harder to steal than the bikes around it.</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.o"><strong>STEP 3: RECOVERY</strong><br>Nationwide, an estimated $350 million worth of bikes go missing every year. And the success rate on returning those bikes is depressingly low: One study concluded only 2.4% of stolen bikes make it back home. Still, that doesn&#x2019;t mean you should sigh and give up if your bike goes missing. </p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.p">First, file a police report. It sounds like a no-brainer, but most bike thefts are never reported.</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.q">&#x201C;People feel like once their bike is gone its gone, so they don&#x2019;t even file a police report,&#x201D; Friedman says. &#x201C;And then there&#x2019;s really nothing we can do.&#x201D;</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.r">Second, don&#x2019;t let embarrassment keep you from seeking help. Inform area bike shops to be on the lookout, spam social media to spread the word, and enroll retroactively with national or local bike registries.</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.s">One thing you <em>shouldn&#x2019;t</em> do is to seek vengeance. Though it&#x2019;s tempting to fantasize about vigilante craigslist meet-ups culminating with you riding off into the sunset, it&#x2019;s not advisable in practice to confront thieves on your own. However, you can still scope craigslist, flea markets and other places that deal secondhand bikes for your missing ride. But if you do get lucky, don&#x2019;t push that luck. Friedman suggests going only so far as to pose as a buyer before looping in law enforcement to handle the confrontation. </p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.t">&#x201C;Personal safety trumps anything,&#x201D; he says. &#x201C;I&#x2019;ve run into too many people that can turn on you in an instant.&#x201D;</p><p data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.4.u"><strong>To recap:</strong> Register your bike. Buy a sturdy lock. (Or two.) And if your bike does go missing, don&#x2019;t give up. Police and digital vigilantes are more than willing to help. Now go outrun that bear.</p></div><div class="grid" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5"><div class="row" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0"><div class="col col-sm-15" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.0"><div class="component-topics" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0"><ul data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0"><li data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-0"><a href="../search?tags=bikes" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-0.0">bikes</a></li><li data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-1"><a href="http://www.gq.com/search?tags=u-locks" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-1.0">u-locks</a></li><li data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-2"><a href="http://www.gq.com/search?tags=protect&#32;your&#32;bike" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-2.0">protect your bike</a></li><li data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-3"><a href="http://www.gq.com/search?tags=bike&#32;thieves" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-3.0">bike thieves</a></li></ul></div></div><div class="col col-sm-5" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.1"><div class="social-share-bottom" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0"><div class="component-social-share default" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves&amp;t=How%20to%20Protect%20Your%20New%20Bike%20from%20Thieves" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves&amp;t=How%20to%20Protect%20Your%20New%20Bike%20from%20Thieves" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0.1">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item twitter" data-href="https://twitter.com/share?text=How%20to%20Protect%20Your%20New%20Bike%20from%20Thieves&amp;via=GQMagazine&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter"><a href="https://twitter.com/share?text=How%20to%20Protect%20Your%20New%20Bike%20from%20Thieves&amp;via=GQMagazine&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhow-to-protect-your-bike-from-thieves" target="_blank" aria-label="Twitter" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0.1">Twitter</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="col col-md-6 col-md-push-1 sticky-wrapper" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.1"><div class="flex-row" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.1.0"><div class="component-stickybox sticky-end" style="height:auto;position:relative;" data-reactid=".1ims7ozcw00.1.1.0.1.0.0"><div class="inner" style="wi